{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> περι-σπάω</b>, <br /> <i>future</i> <b>-σπάσω</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 20.3, 2nd c.AD: Apollonius Dyscolus Grammaticus “de Pronominibus;” 87.15 \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]:—<b>draw off from around, strip off</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator “Epistulae” 9.10 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὸ χλαμύδιον αὑτοῦ π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 19.9, etc.\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]:—<i>middle</i>, <b>strip oneself of</b>, τὴν τιάραν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 3.1.13 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] (so also in <i>active</i>, π. τὴν πορφύραν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Aemilius Paulus” 23). \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>strip bare</b>, περισπάσας ξίφος (Pierson χερὶ σπάσας) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Taurica” 296. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>wheel about</b>, of a general, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 1.76.5 \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; <i>intransitive</i> of the troops, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 3.116.5 \">Refs</a>]; especially <b>wheel twice</b> through a right angle, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Asclepiodotus Tacticus “Tact.” 12.6,a l\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>].; of a horse's bit, οὐ πάνυ π. not <b>pulling</b> it violently <b>round</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Merc.Cond.” 21. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>draw off</b> or <b>away, divert</b>, εἰς τοὐναντίον [τὴν πολιτείαν] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1307a24; τροφὴν εἰς τὸ περικάρπιον 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “de Causis Plantarum” 1.16.2; π. τοὺς Ῥωμαίους 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 9.22.5; τὸν πόλεμον [prev. author] 1.26.1 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; π. τὴν δύναμιν αὐτοῦ <b>draw</b> it <b>away</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Cicero” 45; ἀπὸ τῆς πατρίδος π. τοὺς βαρβάρους 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 20.3; τὸν ἐντὸς.. θόρυβον ἐπὶ τοὺς ἔξω πολέμους 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 6.23; π. περὶ τὰς ἔξω στρατείας τὸν δῆμον [prev. author] 9.43 \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]: —<i>passive</i>, π. ὑπό τινων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PStrassb.” 112.13 (2nd c.BC) \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; πάντῃ τὰς ὄψεις περισπώμενος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “DDeor.” 30.11 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; ἕως τοῦ ἔξω τόπου π. <b>to be drawn away and expanded</b>, opposed to συστέλλεσθαι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Problemata” 863a5. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__III.b</b></Level4> <b>detach</b>, Συρίαν τινός [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Appianus Historicus “Συριακή” 1, compare “Hann.” 56; τινὰς αὐτοῦ τῶν ἀκροατῶν 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “Academicorum Index” p.79 M. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> <b>disturb, vex</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus “Ἐπιτρέποντες” 504, LXX.Eccl.5.19 \">LXX+4th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, ὑπὸ τῶν τελωνῶν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PSI” 3.384.5 (2nd c.BC). \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.3</b></Level3> <b>divert, distract</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.96b, 16oc; π. [τὴν διάνοιαν] ἀπό τινος 4th c.AD: Metrodorus Epigrammaticus “Herc.” 831.4, compare 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “Rh.” 2.53 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus, +others, 1st c.AD: Onosander (Onasander) Tacticus 42.6 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <b>to be distracted</b> or <b>engaged</b>, π. ταῖς διανοίαις [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 15.3.4; ὑπὸ βιωτικῆς χρείας 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 2.29, compare 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “Po.Herc.” 994.24, +others; μηδ᾽ ὑφ᾽ ἑνὸς περισπωμένη ἡ πόλις “IG” 22.1304.7; περί τινος LXX.Sir.41.2; περὶ πολλὴν διακονίαν NT.Luke.10.40: _absolutely_, 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 4.10.3. \">NT+2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.4</b></Level3> <b>steal</b>, ἀργυροῦν ἢ χρυσοῦν ἀνάθημα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Philostratus Sophista “de gymnastica” 45:\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>] —<i>passive</i>, ἅπαντα περιέσπασμαι I <b>have been robbed of</b> all, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus “Ἐπιτρέποντες” 143. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.5</b></Level3> <i>passive</i>, with <i>infinitive</i>, <b>to be compelled</b> to do a thing, περιησπάσθην (sic) ἀνενεγκεῖν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PUniv.Giss.” 19.4 (1st c.AD). \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> Grammars, <b>pronounce</b> a vowel or word <b>with the circumflex</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Apollonius Dyscolus Grammaticus “de Pronominibus;” 33.24, +others, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Theseus” 26, etc.\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; especially on the last syllable, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 2.52f, etc.; π. τὸν τόνον 2nd c.AD: Apollonius Dyscolus Grammaticus “de Pronominibus;” 87.15; τῷ τόνῳ 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 16.495 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; περισπώμεναι [λέξεις] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis “de Compositione Verborum” 11 \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]; π. [προσῳδία] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Dionysius Thrax Grammaticus 630.2, 1st c.AD: Philo Judaeus 1.29; περισπώμενος [φθόγγος] [prev. work] 46. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G4049","accentedUnicode":"περισπάω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0563","matchingForm":"ἀπερισπάστως","stepTransliteration":"aperispastōs","gloss":"undistracted","_zh_tw_Gloss":"而不分心","_es_Gloss":"sin distracción","_zh_Gloss":"而不分心"},{"strongNumber":"G4012","matchingForm":"περί","stepTransliteration":"peri","gloss":"about","_zh_tw_Gloss":"為, 關於","_es_Gloss":"acerca de","_zh_Gloss":"为, 关于"},{"strongNumber":"G4685","matchingForm":"σπάω","stepTransliteration":"spaō","gloss":"to draw","_zh_tw_Gloss":"就拔","_es_Gloss":"sacar","_zh_Gloss":"就拔"}],"shortDef":"(<i>passive</i>) to be distracted distract","mediumDef":"(<i>passive</i>) to be distracted distract <br /><b>to draw off from around; to wheel about; to distract;</b>, <i>passive</i> <b>to be distracted, over busied,</b> <ref='Luk.10.40'>Lk. 10:40</ref>*","stepGloss":"to distract","stepTransliteration":"perispaō","count":1,"_es_Definition":"distraer","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 被拉開, 拖開 (經外含意)<br>2) 被分心, 過度忙碌於, 負荷過多 (路 10:40)","_zh_Definition":"1) 被拉开, 拖开 (经外含意)<br>2) 被分心, 过度忙碌于, 负荷过多 (路 10:40)","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"bận rộn; làm quên đi. περί (G4012) + σπάω (G4685)","_zh_tw_Gloss":"忙亂","_es_Gloss":"distraer","_zh_Gloss":"忙乱"}]}